$interpreted: Bandit Leader: Whew~ it should be safe here. Totemtaff is right ahead. Checkpoints are empty because everyone's attacking the stronghold. Now's our chance.
Hyde: Thank you. We can finish the remaining journey ourselves~
Bandit Leader: What!?
Hyde: Princess, three people. The exact number you ordered.
Naya: Muhahaha, finally. I've been waiting for this moment for too long!
Naya: Haha, that felt good~ If you didn't tell us beforehand that you'll handle everything, I would've kicked their a***** a long time ago!
Hyde: Thank you for your cooperation.
Hyde: Totemtaff is right ahead. Ladies, please go first.
Angelia: Is Sir Hyde not coming with us?

Hyde: The brats are still in the bandits' base. 
Even though it's unlikely that the Kingdom Army bothers them,
Hyde: I still have to go and clear things up.
Angelia: Understood. Then we will wait for you on the borders of Totemtaff.
Hyde: Yes. See you later.

Naya: ... It's getting late... did something happen to Hyde?
Did he get captured... maybe he already betrayed us?
Angelia: No. I trust him. Let's wait a little longer.
Hyde: Apologies for the long wait.
Naya: Long wait indeed! Weren't you only getting the students back home?
Hyde: I will be away from the village for quite a long time. So I had to close the school and deal with all the chores that come with it.
Hyde: Those brats were so delighted when they realized this meant a long holiday!
Angelia: All in all, my sincerest gratitude to you for the will to help us.
Naya: Since we're on the same side now, tell us. Do you have any good ideas to take down Theodore?
Hyde: Theodore has the numbers, but it's not impossible to take him down. I have two plans. It all depends on how many lives princess is willing to sacrifice...
